# mBOLDen Change codebase rules for Cursor

This repo ships the production mboldenchange.org site. Paired with the
`design-system/` folder, which is the canonical reference for brand
voice and visual language.

## Before you write UI code

Read:

- `design-system/README.md` — voice, tone, visual foundations, iconography
- `design-system/SKILL.md` — how to apply the system
- `design-system/colors_and_type.css` — canonical token values (auto-synced)

## Non-negotiables

- Use tokens from `frontend/app/globals.css` and
  `frontend/app/design-tokens.scss`. Never hard-code hex values when a
  `--brand-*` token exists.
- Keep the **tilted-parallelogram identity**: logo tilts `-6.5°`,
  primary buttons skew `-10.25deg` with a clip-path polygon.
- **Archivo Narrow 700** for headlines, **Roboto 400/500/700** for body.
  Loaded via `next/font/google` in `app/layout.tsx`.
- Brand palette only: `#000000`, `#fad826`, `#0091ad`, `#b22f93`,
  `#f8efe0`, `#e2e2e2`, `#ffffff`. No off-brand colors without approval.
- **No emoji.** The single exception is `📄` prefixing PDF download
  links on statement pages.
- **No SVG illustrations of people.** Use real photography from Sanity or
  solid-color placeholders — never illustrate human subjects.

## Voice

- First-person plural: "we / our". Partners, not beneficiaries.
  Communities, not clients.
- Sentence-case headlines (all-caps lives in the logo and eyebrows only).
- Active verbs. "Incubate," "dismantle," "close," "drive" — not "help"
  or "support."
- Em-dashes welcome. Exclamation points are rare.

## When adding a component

1. Check `frontend/components/blocks/` first — an equivalent block may
   already exist (FiftyFifty, CardGallery, CaseStudyHighlight, etc.).
2. Look at `design-system/ui_kits/marketing-web/Components.jsx` for
   reference implementations of the major blocks.
3. Match the CSS-module convention used throughout `frontend/components/`.
   Don't introduce styled-components or Tailwind.
4. New Sanity block types go in `studio/schemaTypes/blocks/`.

## After changing brand tokens

If you edit `frontend/app/globals.css`, `frontend/app/design-tokens.scss`,
or `frontend/styles/_variables.scss`, run:

```
npm run tokens:sync
```

to regenerate `design-system/colors_and_type.css`. CI will fail on drift.
